# SQL-NOTES-
ALL NOTES OR PDF AS A DATA ANALYTICS TO HELP GROWING 💗

A beginner-friendly collection of SQL notes covering the most important concepts, commands, operators, and queries. These notes are designed for students, interview preparation, and anyone starting their SQL journey.

## 📚 Topics Covered

* Introduction to SQL
* SQL Commands

  * DDL (CREATE, ALTER, DROP, TRUNCATE)
  * DML (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE)
  * DQL (SELECT)
  * DCL (GRANT, REVOKE)
  * TCL (COMMIT, ROLLBACK, SAVEPOINT)
* SQL Operators

  * Arithmetic Operators
  * Comparison Operators
  * Logical Operators
  * Special Operators
  * Pattern Matching Operators
* SQL Clauses

  * WHERE
  * ORDER BY
  * GROUP BY
  * HAVING
  * DISTINCT
  * LIMIT
* Aggregate Functions

  * COUNT()
  * SUM()
  * AVG()
  * MIN()
  * MAX()
* SQL Joins

  * INNER JOIN
  * LEFT JOIN
  * RIGHT JOIN
  * FULL JOIN
  * CROSS JOIN
  * SELF JOIN
* Constraints

  * PRIMARY KEY
  * FOREIGN KEY
  * UNIQUE
  * NOT NULL
  * CHECK
  * DEFAULT
* Views
* Indexes
* Subqueries
* Window Functions
* Practice Questions
* Interview Questions

## 🎯 Purpose

These notes are created to:

* Build strong SQL fundamentals.
* Prepare for interviews.
* Practice database concepts.
* Support Data Analytics learning.

